[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(13) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Gird yourselves, and lament.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The priests are exhorted to commence preparations for a national humiliation, beginning with themselves; for the visitation touches them in a vital part: they have no sacrifices to offer to the Lord.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Joel 1:13",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joel 1:13",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Gird yourselves — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Namely, with sackcloth; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and lament, ye priests — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Because the meat-offerings and drink-offerings were cut off: see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joel 1:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Lie all night in sackcloth — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let those priests, whose turn it is to keep the night-watches in the temple, cover themselves with sackcloth, as is usual in times of the greatest calamity; and let them not put it off when they betake themselves to rest, but sleep in sackcloth instead of their ordinary garments.",
        "children": []
      },
