  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Gird yourselves, and lament, ye priests,.... Prepare and be ready to raise up lamentation and mourning; or gird yourselves with sackcloth, and mourn in that, as Aben Ezra and Kimchi supply the words; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 4:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "howl, ye ministers of the altar; who served there, by laying on and burning the sacrifices, or offering incense: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "come, lie all night in sackcloth, ye ministers of my God; that is, come into the house of the Lord, as Kimchi; into the court of the priests, and there lie all night, in the sackcloth girded with; putting up prayers to God, with weeping and lamentations, that he would avert the judgments that were come or were coming upon theme: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the meat offering and the drink offering are withholden from the house of your God; See Gill on Joel 1:9. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "for the meat offering and the drink offering are withholden from the house of your God; See Gill on ",
